Key Match Events: Yusei Kikuchi struck out 12 batters in the Astros' 5-2 victory over the Kansas City Royals
Pre-Game Insights: The Astros were hoping to get a good performance from Yusei Kikuchi, who had a good arm, struck out a lot of batters, and didn't walk many
Post-Match Reflections: Astros manager Joe Espada praised Kikuchi's performance, saying 'Yusei Kikuchi, how good was he?' and 'Our starting pitching has been phenomenal here for a while. Kikuchi adds another level of quality of starts.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Astros have implemented a six-man rotation to help their starting pitchers get extra rest in between their starts
Yusei Kikuchi has gone 3-0 with a 2.57 ERA and 47 strikeouts to just 10 walks in his six starts since arriving in Houston
Others: The Royals never got anything going against Kikuchi, who threw a four-seam fastball and slider combination that produced 17 of his 20 whiffs
